   <ab type="translation"
       xml:id="p0293_translation"
       corresp="#p0293_transcription"> Therefore blessing Noah, God said, <!-- cont. from last page. put together from 
              DRB Genesis 27:23-24 and Genesis 8. The DRB does not translate Noe (remains Noe) but 
               I figure all contemporary readers recognize "Noah" --> 
         I will no more curse the earth for the sake of man <!-- DRB Genesis 8:21 --> 
         for man was made to the image of God. <!-- DRB Genesis 9:6 --> Versicle. 
         This shall be the sign of a covenant between me and the earth: I will set my bow in the clouds of heaven. <!-- DRB Genesis 9:13, sentence order flipped some words
         added--> [For man was made] to [the image of God.] Glory [be to the Father, and to the Son, and to the Holy Ghost. 
         As it was in the beginning, is now, and ever shall be, world without end.]
         [For man was made] to the image [of God.] Magnificat. Anitphon. The first
         [shall be last, and the last first; for many are called, but
         few are chosen.] <!-- DM 80. manuscript flips the order of last/first in that sentence. Prompt assumed from pg 292--> 
         Let us pray. O God, You see that we do not trust in anything that we do of ourselves; mercifully grant that by
         the protection of the doctor of the Gentiles we may be
         defended against all adversities: through our Lord. <!-- DM 81 --> Benedictus. Antiphon. 
         When a very
         great crowd was gathering together and men from evety
         town were resorting to Jesus, He said in a parable: "The
         sower went out to sow his seed." <!-- DM 84, continues to next page --> 
        
